-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Embraer, Gerdau, Vale, Marfrig Alimentos
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-03-20T20:27:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-gerdau-vale-marfrig-alimentos.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index lost 0.6 percent to 67,295.56.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) fell 1.2 percent to 13.65 reais. The
world’s fourth-largest plane maker is scheduled to report 2011
results after the close of trading.  Gerdau SA (GGBR4)  (GGBR4 BS),  Brazil ’s largest steelmaker, fell 2.2
percent to 18.73 reais. BHP Billiton Ltd. said  China ’s steel
output growth rates are slowing.  Vale SA (VALE5)  (VALE5 BS), the world’s
largest iron-ore producer, fell 0.8 percent to 41.60 reais.  Marfrig Alimentos SA (MRFG3)  (MRFG3 BS) fell 1.8 percent to 11.49
reais.  Latin America ’s second-largest beef producer was cut to
underweight from neutral by analysts including Pedro Herrera at
HSBC, citing valuation and the company’s debt levels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
